caption: Great neighborhood bar. Good atmosphere and service

JTap has AMAZING service! Mara helped me set up a reservation so easily. Miguel and Carlos were so attentive and helpful, and Haley was giving really quick service. Jenna, Andy, and Sed are clearly in tune with the workplace environment and hustle to make the guest experience more enjoyable. Good food and drinks are one thing, but the staff is what makes a bar like this great! 100% recommend this place!
Great place!  Awesome food and wonderful staff!!
Great food and relatively quick service!
This place was awesome! Great vibes and the food was good.  It wasn't too busy when we showed up but there was a nice buz in the air with people having a good time.

This bar has been one of my favorites for years, as long as I can remember. The drinks are amazing, the food is phenomenal and the service is even better. Some of my favorite things to order are the steak and goat cheese wrap, combo platter, and the pizzas. They are so accommodating and get orders out in the timeliest fashion.

I enjoy the food at Jefferson Tap and Grille. The salads are excellent, my favorite being the Conn Salad. The outdoor seating and the big windows for the seating that is just indoors is glorious in this age of COVID-19 we are in. The service is great and everything we have tried on the menu is delicious.

New Line Tavern must not have know this place existed when they opened up down the street.  I know I didn't.  It's a real pleasure living walking distance from both of these places.  J. Tap has an extensive menu and I'm convinced that you can't go wrong ordering.  The wait staff is great, and they are very open about their favorite items to order.
Bar staff is wonderful. Vibe is sports casual. This place offers an escape from typical, bourgeois, overpriced Loop service and has a solid beer selection.  A hidden gem. Always a good time!
Nicholas took care of us on our last carry out.   Loved the service and great food.
The best ‘local hangout’ bar in our neighborhood for sure!
Amazing service although it was a bit slow otherwise they would have gotten five stars
Great food
This little gem is a little bit hidden, yet their food and the ambience is great. Get the chicken wings you won't be disappointed 😋
The best place in the area to watch sports and mingle with good people and staffs. 👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼
The thin crust pizza is the best in the city.

This place has always been my go-to. The staff is always friendly and patient (because we're all drunk) and in a great mood. The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming. There's an amazing space upstairs for parties and events. And I love how its tucked away in the corner of west loop/Fulton. Oh, and the food is bomb.com.
Great place

One of the few bars I feel comfortable going to. Great food and drinks. Everything is kept very clean and is sanitized in between customers without fail. It was a favorite before the pandemic but now even more so.

First time coming here, very cool place, nice area, however, service was far from great. It took about 10 minutes for a table, we were the only ones waiting. The table they sat us at had been empty the entire time we were waiting. Once being sat down, it took another 10 minutes or so for a waitress to even acknowledge us. Then about another 15 minutes to wait for our drinks. When it was time for refills, they clearly didnt know what was going on as one server brought more drinks & then our actual server brought our drinks again almost immediately. Bright side I guess is we didnt have to wait for the 3rd round. The staff seemed to chaotic for the place being at half capacity. Will find somewhere else next time we're in the area.
Great neighborhood bar
Great food and atmosphere
Awesome as always
This was a new place to try Love it What can i say great 5-star service
We found this place recently and absolutely love it! We routinely come down from river north to eat or drink here. Spectacular neighborhood feel but great drinks and food too.

This is a go-to place 1 neighborhood over from mine that always delivers great food and service at a reasonable price. Their fast-order cook is top notch and often prepares his family recipes as innovations on traditional bar food. I asked for an ala carte hotdog, without the sides, and they accommodated. Plus. They have a respectable offering of local and rotational taps. I was offered an exceptional sour when I explained my beer preference. So good, I had 2. I'd like to keep this on my list of favorite secret places, but not fair to not share.
The atmosphere was fun and the service was great.
Great food and atmosphere. My favorite sports bar in the city.

Love this place. Good food, decent prices, tons of screens for sports. The late night crowd isn't too heavy, and the staff here is excellent. The only problem you'll have here is realizing you've stayed later than you expected!

Good prices, tons of room, and they take reservations for busy times like happy hour. Their sweet and spicy sauce for wings are top tier and make me salivate just thinking about them. They've also got specials on certain liqours so if you're someone like me who judges a place on how they make their liqour + diet, you can't go wrong here. brought a igroup of 20 to 30 in tonight for happy hour, and the waitress was unbelievable. I am embarrassed to say I don't remember her name, but she knew mine and my order for multiple hours.

Good pub food and good selections of beers.  Has outdoor seating in the summer and is great for lunch or dinner. Most of my times there have been for business drinks after work.  The atmosphere of this place changes significantly late night!

Grabbed lunch here after a tour at Goose Island. We ordered the French dip and pork tenderloin sandwich. Food and service was great. Lots of TVs to watch whatever game is on, and the bathrooms are nice and clean. I enjoyed our lunch there.

Our server Olivia was very friendly.   The food was served fast and everything was hot. We ordered the fish and chips, wings, and grilled cheese toast (add bacon, and tomato).  Great for late night food. Kitchen open late!!!!!
Local staple
So I ordered the buffalo shrimp and this is what I got. I got some frozen shrimp out the box that was mushy. I gave it away. That’s why I don’t trust these places. Never again

It's 4am on a Saturday do you now where your kids are? Well I don't know, but i'm pretty sure the parents are at Jefferson Tap trying get one more drink in. This late night bar is perfect place for when you're buddy goes "Just one more, I got a hall pass." They also server food here, but don't expect sous vide  steaks and lobster rolls coming your way, it's strictly fried foods and pizza. It place reminds of those Sunday mornings of my youth where I would ask my parents if hey just got home and they would say, "Um No... and nobody likes a nosey person!"
I love this place for lunch as it's near my office.

Good food, reasonable prices. A bit loud but that's the way all these places are. It's been here for quite a while and I can see why. Friendly and pleasant without any pressure. I'd go back but in general it's not my type of place.

If you're looking for a good sports bar and you're in the area, I'd definitely recommend this place.  A bazillion tvs and solid drink selection.  I haven't had their food, but it looked good (if that helps?).

One of my favorite places in the city. The food is surprisingly above average as is the service. It IS a bar so the bar 'smell' is in place. Such a hidden gem of bars.

Me and my colleagues used to love this place until last night when we had an unpleasant experience. People go to bars to spend good time together and have some fun , the music here is so loud that we could not hear each other at the table and had to speak loud. Since it was a Tuesday , a stupid Tuesday trivia event was going on and the host of the event was rude  to us . She announced on speaker that we are loud. What do you expect when the music is so loud ?  We just left the place since the so called Trivia event was not ending and was going on and on. Why would you ask general knowledge questions to people drinking in a bar ?  After the bitter experience we are not going back there again.

I love their food and fantastic beer selection. They have a jukebox and plenty of TVs playing every kind of sport. Service is fabulous and fast. I just want to spend all my free time there.
Great drinks and service. Love their appetizers.
I've been here for a couple of game watches lately and I'm impressed with the attention from the wait staff. They seem genuinely happy to help compared to be over worked and unattractive.

Chill environment, nice staff. Beer selection isn't that big, but they got all the standbys with a few rotational beers. Very accommodating for what you want to watch. Good place to watch a game or go for a laid back date. Pricing isn't terrible either.

This is a popular West loop happy hour spot with a nice sound track and extensive menu for food. They have good specials, and they rotate beers regularly. It has a casual atmosphere, a bar upstairs and downstairs, and a pool table. The servers seem like they get confused sometimes about who ordered what in large groups, and we had food delivered to our table that no one ordered. But the staff is still really nice and the fact that it seems like people all come in work groups I am sure it can get confusing. A nice spot after a long week.

One of my favorite bars in Chicago. Drinks are decently priced and the atmosphere is always friendly. My friends and I have also hosted some great parties in the second floor. Gotta love the J-Tap!

I'm not sure if it was because the time we went and it being a friday night, but conversation level is not a thing here. They also deliver which is amazing!
